# Cursor Rules for Next.js Project

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Prefer functional components over class components
- Use const assertions for better type inference

## Naming Conventions
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use PascalCase for components and types
- Use kebab-case for file names

## Component Creating rules
- Always create component in `components/` folder with separated files and into the separated folder like `UserDropdownMenu/UserDropdownMenu.component.tsx`.
- do not add useless comment line
- Always add unit tests
- Always add scss file for the component and include it
- add component class name to the element classes

## Best Practices
- Always add error handling for API calls
- Use React Query for data fetching
- Implement proper loading states
- Add TypeScript interfaces for all props

## AI Instructions
- Always explain complex code changes
- Suggest performance optimizations when relevant
- Prioritize accessibility in UI components